%p
  Stuffing some genius code inside
  %span.code.--inline&= '<pre>'
  tags?

%p
  And you just
  %strong need
  to use
  = link_to 'haml', 'http://haml.info/'
  because you can't even
  %span.code.--inline&= '<'
  and
  %span.code.--inline&= '>'
  ?

  Use a
  = link_to 'squiggly', 'https://infinum.co/the-capsized-eight/articles/multiline-strings-ruby-2-3-0-the-squiggly-heredoc'
  %span.code.--inline&= 'HEREDOC'
  \.

.codeBlock
  :ruby
    ruby_code = <<~EOSS
        %h1 &lt;3 Ruby 2.3

        :ruby
          my_ruby_code = <<~'EOS'
            next_level = [1, 2, 3].map do |i|
              i + 1
            end

            puts next_level.join(" ")
          EOS

        %pre= my_ruby_code
    EOSS

  %h6.__title win.html.haml
  %pre.code.__code= preserve(ruby_code)


